	<div id="help-basics">
		<h4>What is Tiny MCE?</h4>
		<p>Tiny MCE is a word processor-like rich text editor that lets you edit content in a What You See Is What You Get (WYSIWYG) format. It provides a toolbar of formatting options and functions similar to word processors you may already be familiar with.</p>
		<p>The Tiny MCE editor is used by any modules that have one or more fields that accept rich formatted content, for example the Page Content module.</p>
		<p>This help page provides a guide on how to perform the basic tasks in Tiny MCE. If you require more in-depth help, please contact your web developer to arrange a training session.</p>
		<h4>The Editor</h4>
		<p><img src="/extensions/tiny_mce/images/help/editor-example.jpg"></p>
		<p>This example shows the standard toolbar typically offered by most modules that use Tiny MCE. It provides the majority of formatting tools and functions required to do almost everything you need, without compromising the consistency of styles your web developer programmed in to your site.</p>
		<p>Try playing around with the formatting functions available in the toolbar to get a feel for how it works. Here's a quick reference of all the toolbar buttons shown in the above example. The additional help tabs above provide details on some of the more complex, but common, functions.</p>
