			<li><img src="/extensions/tiny_mce/images/help/toolbar-buttons/block-format.gif" alt="Set Block Format" style="vertical-align: middle;"> <strong>Set Block Format</strong><br>
				Set the block format for the content where the cursor is currently location. A block format means either "Paragraph" (default) or a Heading format. Your site should come with at least heading levels 1 to 4, but may have less or more depending on what your web developer setup for you.</li>
			<li><img src="/extensions/tiny_mce/images/help/toolbar-buttons/clear-format-button.gif" alt="Clear Format" style="vertical-align: middle;"> <strong>Clear Format</strong><br>
				Clears all formatting/style for the selected content.</li>
			<li><img src="/extensions/tiny_mce/images/help/toolbar-buttons/draw-table-button.gif" alt="Draw Table" style="vertical-align: middle;"> <strong>Draw Table</strong><br>
				Clicking this button will open a dialog that lets you create a table to insert at the cursor point. The other buttons next to this one become active after you have created a table and your cursor is somewhere in the table. Please consult your web developer for training on proper use of this feature, as setting up nicely formatted tables can be tricky.</li>
		</ul>
